Text.SourceString: Huh? <PlayerName>$player</>?//I’m <NPCName>Dippa</>.
Oh, a corporate employee?//And now you’re a farmer – what a twist, huh?
Oh, good gosh!//Are people really complaining about the dumpster near the community center?
I guess people are going to complain no matter what. The dumpster is just there so we can store our recyclables.//It’s not like anyone breaks their back falling in there or anything.
Oh, good gosh!//Are people really complaining about the dumpster near the community center?
I guess people are going to complain no matter what. The dumpster is just there so we can store our recyclables.//It’s not like anyone breaks their back falling in there or anything.
Hey, thanks for clearing up debris on that lot. A couple of times on my way to paint, I saw you’d done it.//I chill there sometimes, but I don’t have farming tools, so I appreciate your doing that.
Oh, right, right! I meant the lot near <NPCName>Frank</>’s house.
Hey, thanks for clearing up debris on that lot. A couple of times on my way to paint, I saw you’d done it.//I chill there sometimes, but I don’t have farming tools, so I appreciate your doing that.
Oh, right, right! I meant the lot near <NPCName>Frank</>’s house.
How do you avoid getting bit by bugs while clearing up empty lots?
How do you avoid getting bit by bugs while clearing up empty lots?
You never know when inspiration might come. It can be now…//Or an hour from now, or even tonight, when I’m about to fall asleep.
That’s the beauty of art, isn’t it? So unpredictable.
Sadly, many painters only get appreciation after their tragic death.//<portrait=concerned>Things like that make you think, don’t they?
I’m not a fan of the night skies. The darkness and silence only make me feel sadness and sorrow.
Fruits and wildlife are inspirations for me. They’re so pure and free.
Who’s to say mangoes and jackfruits aren’t sentient?//We tend to claim too much, while in reality, we know so little.
We’re not all-knowing beings.//Don’t forget that.
Besides painting on canvas, I collect rocks and use them as a painting surface.//<portrait=happy>They’re very economical.
Meditating first thing in the morning helps me map out my day.//You gotta know what you want in a day in order to get it done, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Some days, small things seem like such a chore, though.
Town life isn’t for me. Socializing is too exhausting.
My brain is clogged. I could really use some inspiration right now… Or a nice long walk.
My brain is clogged. I could really use some inspiration right now… Or a nice long walk.
Town life isn’t for me. Socializing is too exhausting.
Besides painting on canvas, I collect rocks and use them as a painting surface.//They’re very economical.
Town life isn’t for me. Socializing is too exhausting.
Me? Expressionless?//Nonsense.
I’m plenty expressive. I’m smiling right now.//Can’t you see my excitement?
Do you ever kind of feel like you’re missing your old self sometimes?
It’s okay to feel that way, I think.//I miss my performing days all the time.
Me? Expressionless?//Nonsense.
I’m plenty expressive. I’m smiling right now.//Can’t you see my excitement?
Do you ever kind of feel like you’re missing your old self sometimes?
It’s okay to feel that way, I think.//I miss my performing days all the time.
Back in the day, my hair color needed to be natural. You know, a work requirement.//They didn’t let us have a vibrant color. Didn’t want to attract attention, they said.
I can do whatever I want to my hair now, and nobody cares.//I could dye it purple tomorrow, and it wouldn’t matter. It doesn’t make any difference, because I don’t perform anymore.
You don’t look very clean.//<portrait=happy>No offense.
You can get some of my paintings from Socket Electronics.//<NPCName>Luke</> carries some in his store.
Not everyone can follow their passion. And you know what? That’s okay.
Anyone who goes through a life-changing incident knows that. Life goes on.//There are other things in life, believe it or not… There are always other things in life.
Reruns are the best. You know precisely what you’re going to get, and you already know whether or not it’s good! A total time saver.
I said it’s a total time saver… Humph.
Why do I feel like my creativity just isn’t flowing if I’m not in some sort of… Never mind.
Hate self-doubt. It kills the fun.
I hate drinking. The alcohol smell is the worst.
Why do I feel like my creativity just isn’t flowing if I’m not in some sort of… Never mind.
Hate self-doubt. It kills the fun.
<NPCName>Ben</> supplies me with out-of-season items sometimes. He’s strangely very resourceful.
I do wonder from time to time where he gets his stuff.
I miss performing.
Now I can’t even take <NPCName>Emma</> to watch them without being such a bummer about it.
<NPCName>Ben</> supplies me with out-of-season items sometimes. He’s strangely very resourceful.
I do wonder from time to time where he gets his stuff.
Farming isn’t something I can physically do, unfortunately. No more physical work for me.//I did enough in my youth to last the rest of my life. Now I paint, for crying out loud.
Me! I used to do gymnastics five days a week. Now I walk to exercise.//Life is funny like that.
I see these kids at school, and I see hope.//I don’t know what I’m hoping exactly, but it makes it seem like the world isn’t as dark as it feels, you know?
I miss performing.
Now I can’t even take <NPCName>Emma</> to watch them without being such a bummer about it.
My week has been good. What’s up, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Started my day off with some hash browns and hot coffee.
A little sip into an oasis of inspiration, I call it. Ha ha.
<NPCName>Ben</> supplies me with out-of-season items sometimes. He’s strangely very resourceful.
I do wonder from time to time where he gets his stuff.
Why do I feel like my creativity just isn’t flowing if I’m not in some sort of… Never mind.
Hate self-doubt. It kills the fun.
Pufferfish? Oh, I don’t care about things like that.//They own the place, so they’re free to use it however they like.
I could use a nice big jar of fresh jam right now.//Strawberry jam. I should harvest some from my garden. They're in season.

Some of my paintings were painted in tears, so I hope people who look at them get the same morose feeling.//It doesn't need to be sad tears...it can also be happy ones like the sense of beginning in Spring after a long Winter.
An artist should never be afraid to show emotion.//I try very hard to engage with my feelings before creating art.
I like to magnify my feelings and emotions, then I get to work and pour them into the canvas.
Some of my best work is from my dark days.//It just seems easier to create when I’m in the depths.//It's hard to do in Summer.
A good bout of emotion can be addictive. It’s my sole source of inspiration.//Without it, life is boring, and boring is not a way to live.
Our garden is lush this Summer. It feels good to eat our own harvest.
I took some sand from the beach the other day and used it in my latest painting.//It seems fitting, you know. It <Italic>is</> Summer.
Gah… Sunshine.//<portrait=annoyed>I hate it.
Oh my!//If somebody tells me to have a great day one more time…
Oops, sorry. I think I'm having a bad day...if you'll excuse me.
Gah… Another festival is coming up. It’s so exhausting to have to go to so many community activities.//I’d rather stay at home, but I know <NPCName>Emma</> would like to go.
Well, at least there’ll be free mooncakes.
I painted falling leaves the other day. It turned out okay, but I’m not satisfied with it.
It’s generic and bland. It’s missing something, that’s for sure.
I painted falling leaves the other day. It turned out okay, but I’m not satisfied with it.
It’s generic and bland. It’s missing something, that’s for sure.
I really don’t want to walk in the snow.//My boots get all cold and soggy...gah!
I hope you have a fireplace in your cabin with this type of weather.
I really don’t want to walk in the snow.//My boots get all cold and soggy...gah!
I hope you have a fireplace in your cabin with this type of weather.
All of our crops died. It's too cold, I think.
I could use a nice long walk right now.//I want to admire the town being covered with snow before it all melts.
Are you looking for anything?
There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I usually catch up on my reading here.
There isn’t much for me to do when it rains, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> out with his display.
Gah, so gloomy. It’s so depressing.
I’d rather be inside.//I don’t wanna get muddy.
I really have to go.
There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I usually catch up on my reading here.
There isn’t much for me to do when it storms, so I figured I’d help <NPCName>Luke</> out with his display.
I see these kids at school, and I see hope.//I don’t know what I’m hoping exactly, but it makes it seems like the world isn’t as dark as it feels, you know.
Gah, so gloomy. It’s so depressing.
I’d rather be inside.//I don’t wanna get muddy.
Go home, <PlayerName>$player</>. It isn’t safe wandering around in the dark during a storm like this.
My brain is clogged. I could really use some inspiration right now…//<portrait=concerned>Or a nice long walk.
Do you have one of those heaters we can borrow?
Anything can be an inspiration. Flowers, animals… Life events.
My fear is someday I might run out of inspiration. Then what would I make of myself…
I like painting inanimate objects.//The challenge of bringing them to life grounds me.
Some days I get too deep in thought, and all of a sudden, it’s nighttime.
I’m using my favorite brush to paint today.
It makes me happy.//<portrait=happy>Can’t you tell?
Sometimes, I use wool or fresh flowers to paint. It's fun to change things up.

Hmm… How do you know when a painting is finished?//<portrait=happy>You don’t. You let your creativity dictate.//<portrait=normal>If it’s finished, then it will feel finished. Until then, keep painting.
If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be by the school somewhere.
There are birds’ nests everywhere. I think it’s a sign for me.
I need to paint them. Nature chose birds’ nests as my next subject.
If you’re looking for <NPCName>Emma</>, she should be in the woodland somewhere.
Our cottage is pretty small, huh?//I don’t know what we’d do if we decided to get a pet.
If I only had my old job back, I’d be able to afford more than this.
Ah, those pictures are from my performing days. They’re covered with dust now.
I’m on a roll right now.
I feel full of creativity and inspiration.//<portrait=happy>Nature spoke to me today.
I don’t give pointers. You should paint you.//Get drenched in emotion; be honest with yourself.
Only then can you let yourself go on the canvas.//Until then, I’m afraid your paintings will be empty.
It’s nice to see you in such good spirits, <PlayerName>$player</>.
I suppose one of us should be, huh?

By the way, <NPCName>Sam</> was <NPCName>Emma</>’s old boss. He was the one who supported her taco truck in the beginning.//<portrait=happy>He gave her free groceries until she could support herself with the business.
She’s very grateful for them… Oh, <NPCName>Sam</> and <NPCName>Emily</>, I mean.
Ugh… My back is killing me.
Hobbies? Uh… I like to paint.//That’s about it.
You ever think about how your life could have gone if you hadn’t made some little mistake?
Don’t. Dwelling on that stuff will kill your spirit.
As a kid, I loved to paint. It fell by the wayside when I…went down another career path.
But I’m back at it. Didn’t have much of a choice.
I wish I could say other people’s opinions don’t bother me. But everyone needs validation.
I tried meditating, but it didn’t go well. Mindfulness doesn’t stop the back pain.
You're right. I guess it works for some people. Not me, though.
Have you ever had <NPCName>Emma</>’s tacos?//They’re killer.
You ever listen to The Luwaks? Punk band.//Love ’em. Give their latest album a listen if you get time.
You doing okay? Good.
Where are you from, anyway? Never asked.//I mean where in Pokyo City did you live?
The what?? Ah! Interesting. I’ve been a few times.//<portrait=happy>It’s…a bit much for me, at my age.
So, uh… You ever do art, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Meh. It’s a skill. Anyone can learn how, if they’re stubborn enough.

Special.SourceString: I can’t even draw a stick figure!

Text.SourceString: Good. It’s good for you. Self-expression and stuff.
Really? You’ll have to show me your work sometime.
Rain is good for your crops, right?//Neat.
One time, I was doing this huge outdoor painting project, and it started pouring.//I nearly had a panic attack.
But the rain actually washed away parts of it I hated.//The rest I could fix easily.//<portrait=happy>Happy accident. My favorite artist taught me that.
It sure is snowing. Glad you don’t have to farm in this weather.//But then, what ARE you gonna do?
It’s wild to me that this island gets snow when the Summers get so dang hot.
Nature sells. But it’s also comforting, in a way.
The lake has seen better days…but the ocean is even worse.
I actually don’t care if what I paint here sells or not. It makes me happy.
Want to watch TV with me? I love this show.
I like this spot. Got a nice view.
I try to look closely when I paint here. The closer I look, the more unusual my paintings get.
This is a nice spot for painting people.
Can you move a little? You’re in the way.
